==Russian==
===Etymology===
Old Russian [[мечь]], from Slavic ''*mečь'', borrowed from Gothic [[𐌼𐌴𐌺𐌹]], from Germanic.

''Slavic cognates:'' Belarusian [[меч#Belarusian|меч]], Old Church Slavonic [[мечь]], Bulgarian [[меч#Bulgarian|меч]], Slovenian [[meč#Slovenian|mèč]], Czech [[meč#Czech|meč]], Slovak [[meč#Slovak|meč]], Polish [[miecz]].

''Germanic cognates:'' Old English [[mece|mēċe]], Old Saxon [[maki|māki]], Old Norse [[mækir]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /meʧ/

